paragraphs.text:
%python

import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

import xai.knowledge_kit as kk
import tp.tsfresh as tsfresh

import bkzep
from bokeh.plotting import show as bshow
from bokeh.plotting import figure, output_file, output_notebook, reset_output
output_notebook(notebook_type='zeppelin')

paragraphs.title: Load data
paragraphs.text:
%python

from tp.tsfresh.examples.robot_execution_failures import download_robot_execution_failures, load_robot_execution_failures
    
download_robot_execution_failures()
timeseries, y = load_robot_execution_failures()

z.show(timeseries.head(8))

paragraphs.title: Extract features
paragraphs.text:
%python

ts_kit = kk.TimeSeriesAnalysisKit(timeseries, y, col_id='id', col_time='time')
features_df, pvalues_df = ts_kit.extract_relevant_features(feature_set='efficient')
z.show(features_df.iloc[:10, :50])

paragraphs.text:
%python

top50_features = pvalues_df['feature'][:50]

my_feat = z.select("Explain the definition of your selected feature", feat_selector)
p_value = list(pvalues_df[pvalues_df['feature'] == my_feat].loc[:, 'p_value'])[0]

if my_feat:
    print(ts_kit.describe_a_feature(my_feat))

T_y__fft_coefficient__coeff_2__attr_"abs"

    Calculates the fourier coefficients of the one-dimensional discrete Fourier Transform for real input by fast
    fourier transformation algorithm

    .. math::
        A_k =  \sum_{m=0}^{n-1} a_m \exp \left \{ -2 \pi i \frac{m k}{n} \right \}, \qquad k = 0,
        \ldots , n-1.

    The resulting coefficients will be complex, this feature calculator can return the real part (attr=="real"),
    the imaginary part (attr=="imag), the absolute value (attr=""abs) and the angle in degrees (attr=="angle).

import sklearn

def embedding_plot(embed_kind, feature_names, scaler_name='MinMaxScaler',
                   sample_num=200, fig_size=(6, 4), ax=None):

    data_x = temp_df.loc[:, feature_names]
    y_temp = pd.Series(np.copy(y))
    print(type(y), type(y_temp))
    
    if scaler_name:
        scaler = getattr(sklearn.preprocessing, scaler_name)()
        data_x = pd.DataFrame(scaler.fit_transform(data_x))
        data_x.index = y_temp.index
    
    data = pd.concat([data_x, y_temp], axis=1)
    if sample_num < temp_df.shape[0]:
        data = data.sample(n=sample_num)
    y_temp = data.iloc[:, -1]
    
    
    # embedding
    embed_func = getattr(sklearn.manifold, embed_kind)
    embedded_x = embed_func(n_components=2).fit_transform(data.iloc[:, :-1])
    embedded = pd.DataFrame(np.hstack((embedded_x, y_temp.values.reshape(-1, 1))))
    embedded.columns = ['x', 'y', 'label']
    
    # plot
    _, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,8))
    print(embedded['label'].unique())
    sns.scatterplot(x='x', y='y', hue='label', data=embedded, ax=ax)
    plt.title(embed_kind)
    plt.tight_layout()
    
    return ax
 
embed_kind = 'TSNE'
feature_names = temp_df.columns[:10]
scaler_name='MinMaxScaler'
sample_num = 100 
embedding_plot(embed_kind, feature_names, scaler_name, sample_num, fig_size=(8,6), ax=None)

%python

data = timeseries[timeseries['id'] == 4].copy()
values = data['F_x']
time_values = data['time']

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
sns.lineplot(x='time', y='F_x', data=data, ax=ax)

# maximum and minimum points
val_max, idx_max = values.max(), values.idxmax()
time_max = time_values[idx_max]
circle_max = plt.Circle((time_max, val_max), radius=0.2, color='r', 
                        fill=False, linewidth=2)
plt.gca().add_artist(circle_max)
val_min, idx_min = values.min(), values.idxmin()
time_min = time_values[idx_min]
circle_min = plt.Circle((time_min, val_min), radius=0.2, color='g',
                        fill=False, linewidth=2)
plt.gca().add_artist(circle_min)

# plot lines for the mean and the median
val_median, val_mean = np.median(values), np.mean(values)
ax.axhline(y=val_median, label='median', color='darkblue', linestyle='-.')
ax.axhline(y=val_mean, label='median', color='darkblue', linestyle=':')

plt.legend()

plt.show()
